  "content": {
    "visible_text": "Parent Information Pamphlet There is a lot to learn about how to get the most out of your child’s training at the Quantum Dojo. Discipline and ‘buying-in’ to the rules and customs of a martial arts dojo is a considerable part of a student’s training. The following New Student Information PDF file contains a wealth of information for parents of enrolled students at Quantum, including tips on how to wash and wear the uniform, info about testings, Dojo rules, advice for successful attendance, and contact information of Instructors and Assistant Instructors. Printed copies are also available at the Dojo. Versión en español próximamente. Click here to view or download the Quantum Youth Programs New Student Information booklet. Reviews Facebook Community Dojo Quantum Martial Arts is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit in the State of California, and we thrive on the generosity of people like you. All donations are tax-deductible. Quantum’s tax ID number is 26-1534597. No donation is too small, or too large. Whether it’s $20 or $20,000, every cent will be hugely appreciated and put to good use. Support Our Kids Donate now to support our youth scholarship program which allows families in need to train at reduced cost. We believe investment in our community involves investing in our youth. Our Sister Schools Our Seattle Dojo has served thousands of students since opening on Capitol Hill in 1995, and currently offers youth and adult classes in the Central District. Our Portland Dojo was established in 2020, and currently offers youth and adult classes in Southeast Portland. A WordPress.com Website .",
